.TH LOGGERX 1 "February 2026" "loggerx" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
loggerx \- colorized terminal logger with syslog output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B loggerx
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fILEVEL\fR \fIMESSAGE...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B loggerx
prints log entries with a UTC timestamp and level styling.

It can optionally append output to a file and always attempts to write a raw form
of the message to syslog.
.SH LEVELS
EMERGENCY, ALERT, CRITICAL, ERROR, WARNING, NOTICE, INFO, DEBUG, SUCCESS
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-log\-to\-file
Append rendered terminal output to a file.
The default can be set by the
.B LOG_TO_FILE
environment variable.
.TP
.B \-\-log\-file \fIPATH\fR
Path used with
.BR \-\-log\-to\-file .
Defaults to
.B LOG_FILE
if set, otherwise
.BR ./loggerx.log .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI colors in terminal output.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help text and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LOG_TO_FILE
Boolean default for
.BR \-\-log\-to\-file 
(true/false, 1/0, yes/no, on/off).
.TP
.B LOG_FILE
Default path for
.BR \-\-log\-file .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid log level or file logging error.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command usage.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B loggerx INFO "service started"
.TP
.B loggerx WARNING "cache miss"
.TP
.B loggerx --log-to-file --log-file /tmp/app.log ERROR "request failed"
.SH AUTHOR
Alex Atkinson and contributors.
